<br>
And you're probably one of the ones that will complain when it becomes realized that mages can just log on before the raid, do their thing, then log off to save lag.<br>
<br>
Making rods nonlore would be a bad, bad thing.<br>
<br>
For just ONE thing, let us take a look at SoA. I don't have a SoA, but my understanding is, it has a cast time of 7 and gives a 300 point rune. Let's assume our example mage has QS3, SCM3, and a mana pres 3 item.<br>
<br>
Currently, between the 7 seconds to click SoA and 2.25 seconds to cast a rod, it would take (and pardon my possibly super-flawed math.. it's late... hell i just tried to multiply in an addition problem) 23.25 seconds to eat one rod, and the cost of 280 mana? i think? man, got the feeling i did some math wrong :p but anyway, if these stats hold up, that's 98 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
But now a second mage cleared his items from his backpacks into the bank in the bazaar and chatted with friends and browsed the bazaar while summoning 100 mod rods. It takes him 21 seconds to eat a rod (hypothetically instantly getting it from his backpack to his inventory) and it takes him no mana. He gets 660/21 mana/sec.. works out to 188.57 mana/tick, without taking down your pet or anything ! Twice as much as with lore rods! Granted, it took prep time, but now he's ready to duo veeshan's peek with the other mage who did the same. Oh...and let's not even think about the DPS he could sustain with nukes.<br>
<br>
But that's all just talk. He's not really improving downtime since he has an hour of it before he does anything.<br>
<br>
So let's talk about how nonlore rods would really work. These rods have to be made some time, right? Normally, in a raid, a mage overlaps his rod making time with the raid's fighting and buffing times. But since rods aren't lore, he makes them preraid at the IZ, because he wants to be able to nuke during the fight. But everyone who wants a rod has to be there, with him, to get the rod! Now instead of overlapping, he ends up stalling the raid. Woo, that's time efficient. And don't tell me you can make enough rods for each cleric while people are still gathering... if that's so, gather faster. A cleric can consume many rods depending on if you're killing many uber mobs, or just whatever 1 snake or dragon happens to have popped- if it's a long, multi mob raid, the clerics need TONS of mana- if it's 1 mob, they only need a few rods... but it's not worth waiting around while you make them when you could be killing the damn thing.<br>
<br>
The smart mage realizes this: make 100 rods for himself, use SoA to get 188 mana a tick, add bard song and KEI, and churn out a rod every 20 seconds on the raid. He still spends most of the raid making rods, but doesn't cut into anyone's time, only minimally cutting into his guild's dps(lack of mage nukes)~ and that cut is worth it, since the rods he makes sustain the cleric's mana long enough to last through the sliiiightly longer fight.<br>
<br>
Maybe eventually everyone with mana will be full on rods, since you're chain casting them. At this point one of two things happens 1) the mage gets to nuke, finally 2) the raid ends.<br>
<br>
Basically what I'm saying is this: Making rods non lore is not a good fix. Its exploitations are narrow and simple but quite abusable: people running around with 660,000 nearly-instant-mana in their backpacks. But its benefits are questionable: if you're not making rods at the same time you're fighting the mob, then the total time elapsed is twice as long; the mage who presummons rods for everyone is half as time efficient.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd rather overlap my raid time and rod summoning times.<br>
<br>
Non-lore rods is not gonna happen.<br>
<br>
No-drop rods would be the biggest nerf to any class in the history of everquest.<br>
<br>
Give me /drop and ae rod refresh. Two spells to help mages do their own job self-sufficiently, just as the enchanter has tash and color slant to help him keep mobs mezzed without being decapitated when one resists! <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukrilenspiritlink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krilen Spiritlink</A> at: 8/27/02 5:49:36 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
